name: 🌹Eʀɪᴋ Lɪɴᴅǫᴜɪꜱᴛ 🧨🎈🎈🎈🎈🎈 🐶🐹🐻🐼🙈🦝🐺🐗🐄
tweet: #3 Install *all* firmware updates on the new device. Keep applying them and rebooting until there are none left. This step is *vital* or the sCloud restore will *fail*.

tweet: If you want a fast, generic test of your CSV export, try the sqlite command line. Just do ".mode csv" and ".import <file> <table>" and then look at it. If it works there, it will work anywhere.

tweet: @followerwonk One more thing. On the CSV downloads you are sending numbers as quoted strings with grouping commas, that makes most things treat it as TEXT. Ditto, a lot of programs cannot parse your date formatting, a simple "YYYY-MM-DD" / "YYYY-MM-DD hh:mm" would be usable worldwide.
